The fear of the Lord is the beginning of wisdom.
Pride goes before destruction.
A gentle answer turns away wrath.
Iron sharpens iron.
A soft tongue breaks the bone.
The borrower is servant to the lender.
Better a little with righteousness than much with injustice.
Hope deferred makes the heart sick.
As a man thinks, so is he.
Faithful are the wounds of a friend.
A merry heart does good like medicine.
Plans fail for lack of counsel.
A fool despises wisdom and instruction.
The tongue has the power of life and death.
Commit your work to the Lord.
A wise son brings joy.
Better patience than power.
Even a fool is thought wise if he keeps silent.
The Lord detests dishonest scales.
A righteous man walks in integrity.
The way of a fool seems right to him.
Lazy hands make for poverty.
The wise store up knowledge.
Better one handful with rest than two with toil.
Riches do not endure forever.
The prudent see danger and take refuge.
A false balance is an abomination.
The heart plans, but the Lord directs.
Kind words are a honeycomb.
Wisdom is better than strength.
A good name is better than riches.
The lips of the righteous nourish many.
The waywardness of the simple will kill them.
The Lord weighs the heart.
A slack hand causes poverty.
A faithful witness does not lie.
Better to live on a corner of the roof than share a quarrelsome house.
The righteous hate falsehood.
The wise listen to advice.
The fool vents all his feelings.
Truthful lips endure forever.
Better a poor man who walks in integrity.
Wealth gained hastily will dwindle.
The wise inherit honor.
The Lord gives wisdom.
A gossip betrays a confidence.
Better open rebuke than hidden love.
The prudent keep their knowledge to themselves.
A cheerful heart is good medicine.
The righteous are bold as a lion.
The Lord detests lying lips.
Folly brings joy to one without sense.
The eyes of the Lord are everywhere.
A calm spirit gives life to the body.
Wisdom is found on the lips of the discerning.
A fool finds pleasure in evil conduct.
The wise accept instruction.
Better to be patient than hasty.
The Lord blesses the righteous.
Whoever walks in integrity walks securely.
The wise fear the Lord.
A rebuke impresses a discerning person.
The prudent hold their tongue.
The simple believe anything.
Wisdom brings strength.
The Lord hates proud eyes.
A kind heart wins favor.
Wisdom guards the way.
The fools mouth is his ruin.
The righteous care for the poor.
Better wisdom than weapons of war.
A haughty spirit precedes a fall.
The wise seek knowledge.
The Lord makes firm the steps.
A patient man has great understanding.
Folly leads to shame.
The righteous choose their friends carefully.
Wisdom preserves life.
The way of the diligent leads to abundance.
The wise walk with the wise.
A fool shows his annoyance at once.
Wisdom is a shelter.
The Lord rewards righteousness.
Better a dry crust with peace.
The wise avoid extremes.
A foolish son brings grief.
Wisdom calls aloud in the street.
The Lord watches over knowledge.
A faithful person will be richly blessed.
Wisdom is supreme.
The righteous will never be shaken.
The wise inherit honor.
A fool despises correction.
Wisdom brings long life.
The Lord detests a lying tongue.
The prudent act with knowledge.
Wisdom strengthens the wise.
The righteous flourish like a tree.
The wise guard their steps.
The fear of the Lord leads to life.